---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Experience | Luis Leon Pineda"
  description="Professional experience in FPGA development, mixed-signal hardware, embedded systems, automotive diagnostics, technical leadership, and engineering validation."
>
  <section class="page-header container">
    <p class="eyebrow">Professional Background</p>
    <h1>Engineering experience built through design, integration, and hands-on problem solving</h1>

    <p class="hero-description">
      My background combines FPGA and embedded-system development, mixed-signal
      hardware research, board-level testing, automotive electrical diagnostics,
      and technical leadership.
    </p>
  </section>

  <article class="page-content container">
    <section class="experience-section">
      <p class="eyebrow">Engineering Experience</p>

      <article class="experience-entry">
        <div class="experience-heading">
          <div>
            <h2>Undergraduate Research Assistant</h2>
            <p class="experience-organization">
              Texas State University · San Marcos, Texas
            </p>
          </div>

          <p class="experience-date">October 2025 – May 2026</p>
        </div>

        <ul>
          <li>
            Designed, simulated, assembled, and validated custom mixed-signal
            PCBs for a ballistocardiogram (BCG) data-acquisition system used to
            collect physiological measurements.
          </li>

          <li>
            Performed hardware bring-up, verification, and board-level debugging
            with oscilloscopes and logic analyzers to evaluate signal integrity
            and functional performance.
          </li>

          <li>
            Helped relaunch a faculty-developed hardware platform by improving
            component sourcing, manufacturability, cost, and deployment
            scalability.
          </li>

          <li>
            Created the project bill of materials and transferred design
            information, test data, and troubleshooting knowledge to the next
            research team to support long-term project continuity.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="experience-entry">
        <div class="experience-heading">
          <div>
            <h2>BMW Parts Specialist</h2>
            <p class="experience-organization">
              Hendrick BMW of South Austin · Austin, Texas
            </p>
          </div>

          <p class="experience-date">August 2019 – July 2021</p>
        </div>

        <ul>
          <li>
            Supported vehicle repair operations by translating diagnostic
            information into accurate component identification and selection.
          </li>

          <li>
            Coordinated inventory planning and part availability to support
            efficient repair scheduling and reduce service delays.
          </li>

          <li>
            Worked with BMW Technical Support to resolve complex repair cases,
            verify part applicability, and improve first-pass repair accuracy.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="experience-entry">
        <div class="experience-heading">
          <div>
            <h2>BMW Certified Technician</h2>
            <p class="experience-organization">
              Hendrick BMW of South Austin · Austin, Texas
            </p>
          </div>

          <p class="experience-date">May 2018 – August 2019</p>
        </div>

        <ul>
          <li>
            Diagnosed and repaired automotive electrical, electronic,
            mechanical, and electromechanical systems in accordance with BMW
            procedures and quality standards.
          </li>

          <li>
            Used oscilloscopes, digital multimeters, and OEM diagnostic
            software to analyze electrical signals and identify root causes of
            system failures.
          </li>

          <li>
            Worked with CAN, LIN, and automotive Ethernet networks while
            troubleshooting communication and control-system faults.
          </li>

          <li>
            Verified corrective actions through structured post-repair testing
            and complete system validation.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="experience-section">
      <p class="eyebrow">Additional Engineering Experience</p>

      <article class="experience-entry">
        <div class="experience-heading">
          <div>
            <h2>Member, Bobcat Racing</h2>
            <p class="experience-organization">
              Texas State University Formula SAE
            </p>
          </div>

          <p class="experience-date">August 2022 – April 2026</p>
        </div>

        <ul>
          <li>
            Supported Formula SAE powertrain development through component
            evaluation, material selection, and integration of fueling and
            cooling subsystems.
          </li>

          <li>
            Collaborated with a multidisciplinary engineering team during
            vehicle development, testing, and preparation for competition.
          </li>

          <li>
            Contributed recommendations for future telemetry and
            data-acquisition systems to support vehicle performance monitoring.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="experience-entry">
        <div class="experience-heading">
          <div>
            <h2>Self-Initiated Automotive Engineering Projects</h2>
            <p class="experience-organization">
              Electrical, mechanical, and system-integration projects
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <ul>
          <li>
            Applied structured diagnostic, root-cause analysis, and system
            validation methods to complex automotive electrical and mechanical
            projects.
          </li>

          <li>
            Completed a GM LS-series engine integration into a BMW chassis,
            including wiring modifications, electrical integration, mechanical
            adaptation, subsystem testing, and vehicle commissioning.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="experience-section">
      <p class="eyebrow">Leadership and Community Service</p>

      <article class="experience-entry">
        <div class="experience-heading">
          <div>
            <h2>Finance Committee Board Chair</h2>
            <p class="experience-organization">
              Wimberley United Methodist Church · Wimberley, Texas
            </p>
          </div>

          <p class="experience-date">January 2026 – Present</p>
        </div>

        <ul>
          <li>
            Lead finance committee meetings and contribute to budgeting,
            financial oversight, and organizational resource-allocation
            decisions.
          </li>

          <li>
            Helped formalize approval workflows and documentation practices to
            improve accountability, transparency, and reporting accuracy.
          </li>

          <li>
            Co-developed a centralized volunteer-engagement database to improve
            contribution tracking, planning, reporting, and volunteer
            recognition.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="experience-entry">
        <div class="experience-heading">
          <div>
            <h2>Board Chair</h2>
            <p class="experience-organization">
              Bright Beginnings Preschool · Wimberley, Texas
            </p>
          </div>

          <p class="experience-date">January 2025 – Present</p>
        </div>

        <ul>
          <li>
            Chair board meetings and guide decisions involving budgeting,
            policy development, strategic planning, and organizational
            priorities.
          </li>

          <li>
            Partner with executive leadership to identify operational
            improvements and align resources with long-term goals.
          </li>

          <li>
            Facilitate board governance and consensus building while helping
            translate strategic objectives into actionable initiatives.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
